  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Uncertainty quantification was performed across inlet flow rate, rotational speed, and fluid viscosity using a Monte Carlo propagation approach; a screening sensitivity study (Morris method, 500 trajectories) was conducted internally and referenced in the UQ report, confirming that rotational speed and gap clearance dominate hemolysis index variance. Structured sensitivity analysis metadata has been captured in the UQ report document and is verbally summarised in the Model Inputs factor rationale below.",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
  "hasUncertaintyQuantification": true,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-cpb-hemolysis-mrl2",
